      8          /***************************************************************************//**
      9           * Check if the MCU can sleep at that time. This function is called when the system
     10           * is about to go sleeping, with the interrupts disabled. It allows the software to
     11           * cancel going to sleep in case of a last-minute event occurred (window between the
     12           * function call and interrupt disable).
     13           *
     14           * @return  True, if the system can go to sleep.
     15           *          False, otherwise.
     16           *
     17           * @note  This function is called with the interrupt disabled and it MUST NOT be
     18           *        re-enabled.
     19           ******************************************************************************/
